-- Ukraine’s Sovereign Debt Rose 0.6% in April, Ministry Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-05-25T13:46:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/ukraine-s-sovereign-debt-rose-0-6-in-april-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s debt, including state
guarantees, rose 0.6 percent in April as the government borrowed
domestically,  Finance Ministry  said.  State debt increased to $60.897 billion as of April 30 from
$60.5 billion in the previous month, the Finance Ministry, based
in the capital, Kiev, said today in a  statement  on its website.  Domestic debt grew to $22.34 billion from $21.96 billion,
while foreign debt climbed to $24.53 billion from $24.52
billion, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
